modules.description: Handles TCP connections by initializing protocol-specific processing, managing read buffers, and routing requests based on address and socket inputs. Operates on socket and address types to establish and manage network interactions. Used to set up custom connection handlers for real-time data exchange and protocol-specific request routing.

Provides functions to initialize a connection with a specified buffer size and protocol, upgrade the connection to a different implementation, gracefully shut down the connection, and check if it has been closed. Works with a custom connection type and socket abstraction. Used to manage network interactions in a non-blocking manner, such as establishing and terminating WebSocket connections.

Provides HTTP request and response handling, parsing, and serialization using Angstrom and Faraday. Works with byte sequences, strings, and custom protocol structures. Enables building high-performance web clients and servers with support for streaming and custom headers.

Handles HTTP connections by establishing a server-side handler that processes requests and errors. It operates on socket and address types, routing incoming traffic to a specified request handler. Used to build custom HTTP servers with fine-grained control over connection management and error responses.
